<item>
            <title>[SPR-96] DelegatingIntroductionInterceptor does not pick up inherited interfaces</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-96</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DelegatingIntroductionInterceptor does not pick up inherited interfaces. As a consequence, when interface Foo extends Bar, then any attempt to introduce interface Bar using delegation to a FooImpl object will fail in DefaultIntroductionAdvisor.validateInterfaces (line 105).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The underlying cause is that AopUtils.getAllInterfacesAsList does extract all interfaces implemented by an object, but not their superinterfaces. This method&apos;s semantics are not clearly enough defined by the javadoc to say if this really a bug or not, but given the way it is being used I suspect that it is.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fortunately, this issue is relatively easy to work around by declaring FooImpl to implement the Bar interface also, so this is not a critical bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
